704198f-a.folder: Flatbush Avenue & Pacific Street, Brooklyn, NY
704198f-a.text:
Flatbush Ave., west side, just north of its intersection with Pacific Street, showing the B.M.T. Culver Elevated Lines in the foreground. In the
background, is the Long Island Railroad Depot.
May 11, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

706168f-a.folder: Pacific Street & Flatbush Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
706168f-a.text:
621 Pacific Street, north side, at the intersection of Flatbush and Fifth Aves. Also seen is Flatbush Ave., east side, and north from Pacific Street.
October 6, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

704200f-a.folder: Flatbush Avenue & Pacific Street, Brooklyn, NY
704200f-a.text:
161 to 181 Flatbush Avenue, east side, south from Paoific Street to Fifth Avenue. The buildings occupying this block, with the exception of No. 177 (3oodwear
Sporting Goods), were later demolished.
July 23, 1934
(2)
The same location. The building is No. 177. The parking space replaced the houses numbers 161 to 175. On the right, at Fifth Avenue, is a gasoline station,
where stood houses numbers 179 to 181.
May 17, 1940
L. Sperr
